data.description: This house is a HOME that is inviting, warm and extremely Impressive.  A two -story colonial with a large and flowing floor plan is located in North Wilmington.  This freshly painted Brandywine Hundred home offers 4 bedrooms, 2-and a half bath, second floor laundry, and 2 car garage.  The home has recently been updated and offers detailed craftsmanship in every room.   The kitchen with all new stainless-steel appliances, plenty of cabinets with granite countertops, and a breakfast bar flows nicely into the dining room with chair railing, and a lighted glass cabinet above the convenient beverage cooler.    The living room has plenty of room for furniture and the bay window provides lots of natural light. The first-floor den is a wonderful retreat complete with bamboo flooring, a gas fireplace with black travertine surround and hearth and an exotic hardwood mantle.  The basement offers a large, finished area for a great family room.  There is ample storage in the unfinished section.  Upstairs the primary bedroom welcomes you with a large area with wall-to-wall carpet, good size walk-in closet and a master bath that is sure to please.  Finish the upstairs with laundry with barn door, full bath with deep tub, and 3 more bedrooms all with carpet.  Enjoy some downtime in the 3-season room with two accesses to the large back fenced in yard with two patios. and no neighbors behind.  The added touches you will see as you tour will confirm the quality of the upgrades and workmanship.  Enjoy you will not be disappointed.  Convenient to I95, 202, Philadelphia Airport, shopping and restaurants.   No need to worry about snow removal, Shipley Road will be cleared at first snowflake, bus route within walking distance, walking park within minutes.  Interested in bringing your mortgage payments down to size.  Contact Alan Jacobs, Mortgage Advisor, Weichert Realtors and talk about a BUYDOWN loan.
